    {
      "id": "PopularPost39718",
      "post_content": "It's a nice remake of [Delusions of Grandeur](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delusions of Grandeur) with half the life points used, but without any upkeep cost.  \n  \nThis makes it far less useful for a [Donate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Donate) combo, but it still has decent uses with cards that interact with lifeloss and lifegain: The aforementioned [Sanguine Bond](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sanguine Bond) or [Ageless Entity](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ageless Entity) for instance; or [Children of Korlis](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Children of Korlis)/[Tainted Sigil](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tainted Sigil) to offset the drawback (or even gain a load of life again when saccing two).  \nWhen playing against mono red or black decks (or those without enchantment removal in general) this also makes some cheap life gain, which certainly isn't a common thing for blue.",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost39718\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">It's a nice remake of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Delusions of Grandeur\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delusions of Grandeur\">Delusions of Grandeur</a> with half the life points used, but without any upkeep cost.<br/><br/>This makes it far less useful for a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Donate\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Donate\">Donate</a> combo, but it still has decent uses with cards that interact with lifeloss and lifegain: The aforementioned <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sanguine Bond\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sanguine Bond\">Sanguine Bond</a> or  <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ageless Entity\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ageless Entity\">Ageless Entity</a> for instance; or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Children of Korlis\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Children of Korlis\">Children of Korlis</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tainted Sigil\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tainted Sigil\">Tainted Sigil</a> to offset the drawback (or even gain a load of life again when saccing two).<br/>When playing against mono red or black decks (or those without enchantment removal in general) this also makes some cheap life gain, which certainly isn't a common thing for blue.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '39718'); return false;\">\r\n                                    